@startuml
title POST /api/v1/registration/accounts — LOCAL STUDENT (201 Created)
autonumber

actor Client
participant "register_account()\n_register_local()" as View
participant "StudentInvite\nRegisterSerializer" as Serializer
participant "password_strength\n_errors()" as PwdCheck
participant "validate_registration\n_code()" as Validate
participant "redeem_student\n_invite()" as Redeem
participant "create_user_from\n_payload()" as CreateUser
participant "_ensure_student\n_enrollment()" as Enroll
database Postgres

Client -> View: POST /registration/accounts\n{method: "LOCAL", code, firstName,\nlastName, password, confirmPassword}
View -> Serializer: is_valid(raise_exception=True)
Serializer -> Serializer: reject unknown fields\n(StrictFieldsSerializer)
Serializer --> View: validated data

View -> View: password == confirmPassword?
View -> PwdCheck: password_strength_errors(password)
PwdCheck -> PwdCheck: >= 8 chars, upper, lower,\ndigit, special char
PwdCheck --> View: [] (no errors)

View -> Validate: validate_registration_code(code)
Validate -> Postgres: SELECT registration_codes\nWHERE code_hash = ?
Postgres --> Validate: RegistrationCode (STUDENT type)
Validate --> View: RegistrationCode

note over View: code_type == STUDENT\n-> student registration path

== @transaction.atomic ==

View -> Redeem: redeem_student_invite(validated_data)
Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT registration_codes\nWHERE code_hash = ?\nFOR UPDATE
Postgres --> Redeem: RegistrationCode (locked)
Redeem -> Redeem: validate code_type == STUDENT
Redeem -> Redeem: validate course_id exists
Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT courses WHERE id = ?
Postgres --> Redeem: Course

Redeem -> Redeem: generate_managed_username()\n_normalize -> _seed -> 8-char
Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT EXISTS app_users\nWHERE username = ?
Postgres --> Redeem: False (unique)

Redeem -> CreateUser: create_user_from_payload(\nrole=STUDENT, creator=None)
CreateUser -> Postgres: INSERT INTO app_users\n(username, password_hash, name, email)
Postgres --> CreateUser: User created
CreateUser -> Postgres: DELETE FROM user_roles\nWHERE user_id = ?
CreateUser -> Postgres: INSERT INTO user_roles\n(user_id, role=STUDENT)
CreateUser -> Postgres: SELECT EXISTS student_profiles\nWHERE user_id = ?
Postgres --> CreateUser: False
CreateUser -> Postgres: INSERT INTO student_profiles\n(user_id, created_by=user, consent=False)
CreateUser --> Redeem: User

Redeem -> Enroll: _ensure_student_enrollment(user, course)
Enroll -> Postgres: SELECT student_profiles\nWHERE user_id = ?
Postgres --> Enroll: StudentProfile
Enroll -> Postgres: SELECT enrollments\nWHERE course_id = ? AND student_profile = ?
Postgres --> Enroll: NULL (not enrolled)
Enroll -> Postgres: INSERT INTO enrollments\n(course_id, student_profile, status=ACTIVE)
Enroll --> Redeem: (Enrollment, already=False)

Redeem -> Postgres: UPDATE registration_codes\nSET times_used += 1\n(deactivate if max reached)
Redeem --> View: (User, Enrollment)

== end transaction ==

View -> View: RefreshToken.for_user(user)\ngenerate JWT access + refresh tokens
View -> View: build_user_response(user, tokens)

View --> Client: 201 Created\n{message, username, name, email,\naccessToken, refreshToken, role,\ncourseId, createdNewUser: true}
@enduml
